<h2>Chapter 3: Random Variables & Distributions</h2>

<h3>Discrete & Continuous Variables</h3>
<p>Discrete variables take finite values; continuous variables take infinite values.</p>

<h3>Probability Mass Function (PMF)</h3>
<p>PMF assigns probabilities to discrete random variables.</p>

<h3>Probability Density Function (PDF)</h3>
<p>PDF describes probability distribution for continuous variables.</p>

<h3>Cumulative Distribution Function (CDF)</h3>
<p>CDF gives probability that a variable is less than or equal to a value.</p>

<h3>Binomial, Poisson & Normal Distributions</h3>
<p>These are widely used probability distributions in statistics.</p>

